rComments: The test is very easy and the midterm average I think would be A, but for the final essay, the average is c-. Also, do not have any quiz. Have midterm but do not have the final exam, have paper and group project.

She is extremely strict and unappreciative when it comes to student's hardwork. You would literally get a C- (the average for our term paper) because she assumes no thoughts/efforts were put in. Also very subjective and not willing to take any words from students as a new professor.

First of all, she is totally boring. Her voices and pronunciation make people want to fall asleep. Secondly, her academic level isn't good enough. She cannot even remember Liu Bang's name in the lecture. Her lectures make no sense. Not helpful at all. She is the worst professor in the department I've ever seen.

For me, this course has been a breeze so far, since I'm somewhat fluent at Mandarin. I usually only attend the lectures/tutorials only if I'm required to do a quiz or hand in homework, though I would not recommend doing that as a lot of lecture material is testable. Course schedule and lecture time is very well organized and quizzes are fairly easy

I love Xu laoshi! Sure, you won't succeed unless you are enthusiastic about learning the language because the class material can be challenging, but she is always there for you and super friendly. Her tests are fair, as long as you do your homework you'll get an A. She is also very knowledgeable you will learn so much more than just the language.
